why must Your Majesty use
Coptis chinensis in the medicine?

14
00:02:25,320 --> 00:02:27,930
That servant is full of ill tricks.

15
00:02:28,600 --> 00:02:30,800
Her vile intention is oozing out of her.

16
00:02:30,950 --> 00:02:35,640
Coptis chinensis clears the heat
and poison. It's just right for her.

17
00:02:38,790 --> 00:02:39,870
By the way,

18
00:02:42,030 --> 00:02:45,360
any other prescription that
are even more bitter?

19
00:02:45,750 --> 00:02:47,840
Your Majesty, why don't you just kill her?

20
00:02:47,840 --> 00:02:50,040
How could you torment people like this?

21
00:02:56,600 --> 00:02:58,300
I'm a wise ruler.

22
00:02:59,079 --> 00:03:02,410
How could a wise ruler just
kill someone who carries merits?

23
00:03:02,640 --> 00:03:08,140
If words got out, won't I be criticized
as being so petty?

24
00:03:08,640 --> 00:03:10,520
Yes, I misspoke just now.

25
00:03:10,640 --> 00:03:13,040
Your Majesty, in terms of
the most bitter medicine,

26
00:03:13,040 --> 00:03:16,120
gold thread, akebia, and
gentian are all very bitter plants,

27
00:03:16,120 --> 00:03:19,030
but the most bitter is bitter ginseng.

28
00:03:25,200 --> 00:03:28,390
Starting from today, for all her meals,

29
00:03:28,640 --> 00:03:31,630
give her a different
bitter medicine every meal.

30
00:03:32,350 --> 00:03:35,820
If she refuses to drink it,
use of force is allowed.

31
00:03:37,640 --> 00:03:40,100
A bitter medicine is
good for one's illness.

32
00:03:40,220 --> 00:03:44,620
I'm doing because I want to save
the life of my saviour.

33
00:03:46,240 --> 00:03:47,860
Do you know what I mean?

34
00:03:48,180 --> 00:03:51,920
Yes, I will strictly abide to
Your Majesty's order.

35
00:03:57,280 --> 00:04:01,290
Chief Li, if His Majesty
really hates Miss Ying Luo,

36
00:04:01,680 --> 00:04:05,360
he could just give her poison.
Why must he torment her like this?

37
00:04:05,710 --> 00:04:07,290
His Majesty told us.

38
00:04:07,400 --> 00:04:11,160
Although Wei Ying Luo was ruthless to him,
but she cured his illness.

39
00:04:11,160 --> 00:04:13,000
She should be rewarded for her work.

40
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:15,030
We could tell the world she died
from the illness,

41
00:04:15,030 --> 00:04:16,410
won't that be simpler?

42
00:04:23,480 --> 00:04:24,810
What do you mean?

43
00:04:24,920 --> 00:04:26,960
It's so hard to predict one's fate.

44
00:04:27,080 --> 00:04:30,600
The heart of the Emperor is not
for lowly peasants like us to predict.

45
00:04:30,600 --> 00:04:33,120
Just do whatever His Majesty
has instructed.

46
00:04:33,120 --> 00:04:35,130
Stop worrying.

47
00:04:35,770 --> 00:04:36,909
Got it.

